#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Pabbatavagga"
msgstr "1. Mountains"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn46.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Himavantasutta"
msgstr "1. The Himalaya"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.63"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.1:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, himavantaṃ pabbatarājānaṃ nissāya nāgā kāyaṃ "
"vaḍḍhenti, balaṃ gāhenti;"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, dragons grow and wax strong supported by the Himalayas, the "
"king of mountains."

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.3"
msgid ""
"te tattha kāyaṃ vaḍḍhetvā balaṃ gāhetvā kusobbhe otaranti, kusobbhe otaritvā "
"mahāsobbhe otaranti, mahāsobbhe otaritvā kunnadiyo otaranti, kunnadiyo "
"otaritvā mahānadiyo otaranti, mahānadiyo otaritvā mahāsamuddasāgaraṃ "
"otaranti; te tattha mahantattaṃ vepullattaṃ āpajjanti kāyena;"
msgstr ""
"When they’re strong they dive into the pools. Then they dive into the lakes, "
"the streams, the rivers, and finally the ocean. There they acquire a great "
"and abundant body."

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.4"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya satta "
"bojjhaṅge bhāvento satta bojjhaṅge bahulīkaronto mahantattaṃ vepullattaṃ "
"pāpuṇāti dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant develops and cultivates the seven awakening "
"factors depending on and grounded on ethics, acquiring great and abundant "
"good qualities."

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.5"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya satta bojjhaṅge "
"bhāvento satta bojjhaṅge bahulīkaronto mahantattaṃ vepullattaṃ pāpuṇāti "
"dhammesūti?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant develop the seven awakening factors depending on "
"and grounded on ethics, acquiring great and abundant good qualities?"

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.6"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ "
"virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant develops the awakening factor of mindfulness, which "
"relies on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripens as letting go."

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.7"
msgid "dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe …"
msgstr "They develop the awakening factor of investigation of principles …"

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.8"
msgid "vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe …"
msgstr "They develop the awakening factor of energy …"

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.9"
msgid "pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe …"
msgstr "They develop the awakening factor of rapture …"

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.10"
msgid "passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe …"
msgstr "They develop the awakening factor of tranquility …"

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.11"
msgid "samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe …"
msgstr "They develop the awakening factor of immersion …"

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.12"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ "
"vossaggapariṇāmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"They develop the awakening factor of equanimity, which relies on seclusion, "
"fading away, and cessation, and ripens as letting go."

msgctxt "sn46.1:1.13"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya satta bojjhaṅge "
"bhāvento satta bojjhaṅge bahulīkaronto mahantattaṃ vepullattaṃ pāpuṇāti "
"dhammesū”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant develops and cultivates the seven awakening factors "
"depending on and grounded on ethics, acquiring great and abundant good "
"qualities.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.1:1.14"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
